New York â€™s subway stations will
receive wireless Internet service as part of a multiyear rollout
plan that will eventually allow smartphone, tablet and computer
users to access the Web while waiting for the train.  The Wi-Fi service, provided by  Boingo Wireless Inc. (WIFI) , will
be available throughout Manhattan, Brooklyn, Bronx and Queens,
Boingo said today in a statement. The service will be available
to Boingo subscribers and customers of its partners, which
